’Щ@37f5e0c897711fa938dd0d83790bf49598a14547d52f3016e3c9535e4edf8b6aЪЃTitle: title: encode base32hex
Path: Examples
Content:
Encode a binary value
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[57 6E AD] | encode base32hex
ATNAQ===

```
Encode a string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "hello there" | encode base32hex
D1IMOR3F41Q6GPBICK======

```
Don't apply padding to the output
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "hello there" | encode base32hex --nopad
D1IMOR3F41Q6GPBICK

```
’Щ@d379a3a8eecb111bcf9765928a2fbd5cf7dfffd4e885a03ecde554f90046bcd1ЩіTitle: title: encode base32hex
Path: Notes
Content:
This command uses an alternative Base32 alphabet, defined in RFC 4648, section 7.
Note this command will collect stream input.
